The atomic weight is the sum of the masses of these particles. 1. The mass of a proton is approximately \(1.007276\) amu. 2. The mass of a neutron is approximately \(1.008665\) amu. Calculating the total mass of two protons and two neutrons: \[ 2 \times 1.007276 \, \text{amu} = 2.014552 \, \text{amu} \] \[ 2 \times 1.008665 \, \text{amu} = 2.017330 \, \text{amu} \] Adding these together: \[ 2.014552 \, \text{amu} + 2.017330 \, \text{amu} = 4.031882 \, \text{amu} \] Rounding this value to five decimal places, we get: \[ 4.03188 \, \text{amu} \] Thus, the atomic weight of ${He}^{2+}$ is \boxed{4.03188} amu.
